Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at Nucor Steel Auburn in New York, emphasizing the administration's commitment to American steel and addressing the ongoing crisis of illegal immigration at the southern border. Pence called for immigration reform and urged Congress to pass legislation to secure the border and close loopholes in immigration laws. He also highlighted the Trump administration's efforts to roll back federal regulations, promote American energy, and fight for fair trade deals. Pence thanked Nucor Steel for its investments in America and highlighted the company's contribution to job creation. He concluded by expressing confidence that America will become safe, prosperous, and great again.